<Project Sdk="Microsoft.NET.Sdk">

	<PropertyGroup>
		<TargetFramework>net10.0</TargetFramework>
		<ImplicitUsings>enable</ImplicitUsings>
		<Nullable>enable</Nullable>
		<Version>4.9.2-rc.27</Version>
		<PackageReleaseNotes>v4.9.2-rc.27: Critical multi-peer fix - `P2PWebRtcBridge.AttachToSwarm`'s `wire.OnClose` handler unconditionally fired `_transport.UnregisterPeer` on the canonical BT peer id, including for loser wires from the BEP-10 handshake race that close before capability exchange completes. Each loser-close called `HandlePeerDisconnected(canonical)` which removed the surviving peer from `P2PSwarmCoordinator._peers`, manifesting as `coord.PeerCount` stuck at &lt;expected&gt; despite the bridge correctly seeing 2+ extensions. Diagnosed against `MultiPeer_Concurrent_10_DispatchedOverRealWebRtc_BitExact`: bridge.ComputePeerCount transiently spiked to 4-5 then settled to 2, each wire close evicting the surviving peer; coord saw 1 of 2 expected peers, 60s timeout, retry retry retry, dispatch ultimately failed. Fix: wire.OnClose now early-returns unless BOTH (a) `wasNotified` (this wire actually completed `NotifyCanonical` -&gt; capability exchange completed -&gt; contributed an entry to _peers) AND (b) `isLastWireForCanonical` (no other wires for this canonical BT peer id remain). Loser wires that close before capability exchange are silent per-wire cleanup only. Verified 3/3 trials pass in ~9s each (was: 0/3 with 60s peer-discovery timeouts + 90s dispatch timeouts). Includes the rc.26 bridge dedup, push-back-first, and SpawnDev.WebTorrent 3.2.2-rc.1 dep bump unchanged.</PackageReleaseNotes>
		<GeneratePackageOnBuild>True</GeneratePackageOnBuild>
		<GenerateDocumentationFile>true</GenerateDocumentationFile>
		<EmbedAllSources>true</EmbedAllSources>
		<DebugType>Embedded</DebugType>
		<Title>SpawnDev.ILGPU.P2P</Title>
		<Authors>LostBeard</Authors>
		<Description>P2P distributed GPU compute via SpawnDev.WebTorrent. AcceleratorType.P2P â€” the 7th ILGPU backend. Distributes kernels across connected devices via WebRTC. Scan a QR code, contribute GPU power.</Description>
		<PackageProjectUrl>https://github.com/LostBeard/SpawnDev.ILGPU</PackageProjectUrl>
		<PackageLicenseFile>LICENSE.txt</PackageLicenseFile>
		<RepositoryUrl>https://github.com/LostBeard/SpawnDev.ILGPU.git</RepositoryUrl>
		<RepositoryType>git</RepositoryType>
		<PackageTags>P2P;WebRTC;WebTorrent;ILGPU;GPU;DistributedCompute;GPGPU</PackageTags>
		<LangVersion>latest</LangVersion>
		<AllowUnsafeBlocks>true</AllowUnsafeBlocks>
	</PropertyGroup>

	<ItemGroup>
		<None Include="..\LICENSE.txt" Pack="true" PackagePath="\" />
	</ItemGroup>

	<ItemGroup>
		<ProjectReference Include="..\SpawnDev.ILGPU\SpawnDev.ILGPU.csproj" />
		<PackageReference Include="SpawnDev.WebTorrent" Version="3.2.2-rc.1" />
	</ItemGroup>

</Project>
